        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1729198731
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It should be relatively easy to adapt the existing extension for <code>Nat.sqrt</code>.</p>",
        "id": 477523426,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1729198795
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"197836\">Jireh Loreaux</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/sqrt.7B25.7D.20.3D.205.20.3F/near/477523287\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>?? But then it can't return a proof?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>or use sympy to suggest the form and use LEAN to prove it? I don't think this is the way to go but just saying out my thought.</p>",
        "id": 477523521,
        "sender_full_name": "RedPig",
        "timestamp": 1729198820
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My comment was directed at Ruben's suggestion, not yours, sorry for the confusion.</p>",
        "id": 477523642,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1729198874
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the overhead of calling out to sympy is probably not worth it, either in time or complexity</p>",
        "id": 477523717,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1729198912
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though it's an interesting idea</p>",
        "id": 477523798,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1729198937
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>another question: currently the proofs stuck at <br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>∗</mo><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">3 * √25 - 8 = 7</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">8</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">7</span></span></span></span><br>\nfrom a human perspective, we should be able to reformat it as <br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>∗</mo><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">3 * √25 = 7 + 8</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7278em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">7</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">8</span></span></span></span><br>\nand then<br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>∗</mo><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">3 * √25 = 15</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">15</span></span></span></span><br>\nand then<br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">√25 = 5</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">5</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>Is there function in LEAN can auto-transform in this way or it is all need to be manual?</p>",
        "id": 477524814,
        "sender_full_name": "RedPig",
        "timestamp": 1729199483
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How would Lean know that this is the form you want? (i.e., how would it know you wouldn't want <code>3 = 15 / √25</code>, or any other variation?)</p>",
        "id": 477524969,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1729199564
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Somewhere in Zulip there is a simproc that can reduce squares to <code>k * sqrt s</code> with <code>s</code> square-free. It's not appropriate for normnum (other than for perfect squares) since normnum is for calculating a normal form that's integral or rational.</p>",
        "id": 477526734,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1729200437
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(I believe the simproc is just for Nat.sqrt)</p>",
        "id": 477526795,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1729200467
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Found it, and it was for Real.sqrt: <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Should.20these.20surds.20be.20simplified.20with.20norm_num.3F/near/444362938\">https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Should.20these.20surds.20be.20simplified.20with.20norm_num.3F/near/444362938</a></p>",
        "id": 477527141,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1729200622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"742049\">RedPig</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/sqrt.7B25.7D.20.3D.205.20.3F/near/477524814\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>another question: currently the proofs stuck at <br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>∗</mo><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">3 * √25 - 8 = 7</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">8</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">7</span></span></span></span><br>\nfrom a human perspective, we should be able to reformat it as <br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>∗</mo><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">3 * √25 = 7 + 8</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7278em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">7</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">8</span></span></span></span><br>\nand then<br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>∗</mo><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">3 * √25 = 15</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">15</span></span></span></span><br>\nand then<br>\n<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>√</mtext><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">√25 = 5</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.2em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">√25</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">5</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>Is there function in LEAN can auto-transform in this way or it is all need to be manual?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">√</span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">suffices</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">√</span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">polyrith</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sqrt_eq_cases</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>i.e. if you tell it the form you want, it's plain sailing.</p>",
